Global Lipid Panel Testing Market Definition

A lipid panel or lipid profile test assesses the risk for cardiovascular disease in a person. It is a combination of various blood tests, which is performed to measure the levels of 4 types of lipids in our blood such as total cholesterol, low-density lipoprotein cholesterol, high-density lipoprotein cholesterol, and triglycerides.

The report covers the current estimated and forecasted data for the Global Lipid Panel Testing Market on a global and regional level. The report provides an in-depth analysis of the Global Lipid Panel Testing Market for the period 2019 – 2026, wherein 2019 is the base year and the period from 2020 to 2026 is the forecast period.

The Global Lipid Panel Testing Market is segmented by Disease, End-User and Region. The report provides qualitative and quantitative insights on the lipid panel testing industry trends and a detailed analysis of the market size and growth rate of all segments in the market.
Global Lipid Panel Testing Market Dynamics

The lipid panel is used as part of a cardiac risk assessment to help determine your risk of heart disease and to help make decisions about what treatment may be best if you have borderline risk, intermediate-risk, or high risk. Large numbers of laboratories conducting lipid testing are driving the global market. Automated, rapid and sensitive lipid testing procedure and the need for high-quality medical solutions are propelling the global market.
