Hyperlipidemia has no symptoms, so the only way to detect it is a lipid panel or a lipid profile.Cardiovascular disease caused over 18 million deaths in the world in 2005. Of these deaths, eight million (44%) occurred in people under 60 years of age and 80% took place in low- and middle-income countries. By 2015, World Health Organisation set a goal of reducing the global rate of death from chronic diseases by 2% each year. This situation led to creating future opportunity for the global market.
Diagnostic Laboratories conduct lipid panel tests in the diagnosis and treatment procedures.

Diagnostic laboratories play a significant role in the care continuum be it for diagnosis, prevention, monitoring or treatment. Large labs have successfully opened collection centres across the globe, including in the most backward districts, to enable them to serve the remotest populations suffering from cardiovascular disorders.

Laboratories across the globe are trying to adapt with automated lipid panel emerging that helps to overcome unmet biomedical research demands. The diagnostics industry accounts for 4–5% of total healthcare expenditure, use a lipid tests panel, which helps in delivering affordable diagnostic healthcare to a population, thus further contributing to the global lipid panel testing market.
